parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to move safely, potentially leading to loss of vehicle control or injury in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt becomes stuck in the track
the seatbelt retractor locks up
the seatbelt does not retract upon opening of the door
the seatbelt retracts too tightly
the seatbelt warning light goes off intermittently
the seatbelt buzzer goes off continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent malfunction of the seatbelt can cause the seatbelt to become stuck or not function properly, potentially leading to injury or loss of vehicle control in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor locks up intermittently
the seatbelt does not retract upon opening of the door
the seatbelt warning light goes off intermittently
the seatbelt buzzer goes off continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passive restraint system can cause the seatbelt to malfunction, potentially leading to injury or loss of vehicle control in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor locks up
the seatbelt does not retract upon opening of the door
the seatbelt warning light goes off intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seatbelt buckle and retractor can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the seatbelt may not properly restrain the occupant.
symptoms: The seatbelt buckle will not stay latched
the seatbelt is out of track
exposed wires are visible
the motor runs constantly when the key is in the ignition
and the automatic shoulder belt is inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inoperative automatic shoulder belt can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The automatic shoulder belt does not function
the lap belt is operational but the automatic shoulder belt is not.
